(3, 'Councillor''s Watch', 'A flash of light catches your eye as you scan over a pile of rubble.  When you move the rocks away, you find a lovely gold watch!  You''ve done it!', 1, 276, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(4, 'Fragment of the Timepiece', 'You spot a strange looking stone on the ground, and carefully check the note you were given.  It appears to be a match!  Wonderful, you''ve found the fragment!', 1, 281, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(5, 'Daggerfang Matriarch''s Egg', 'As you venture around the swamplands, you stumble across a small nest of eggs.  You''ve found it!  Carefully, you remove one of the eggs, and tip-toe away.', 1, 293, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(6, 'Iron Dust Sample Stash', 'Using your Tarnished Map, you manage to track down the location of a small stash of Iron Dust Samples!', 1, 183, 3, 1000, 0, 0),
(7, 'Discovery: Tiny Blue Sandstone', 'You stumble across a curious looking pile of sand thanks to your Arcane Detection Stone, and discover a Tiny Blue Sandstone!', 1, 266, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(8, 'Discovery: Tiny Crystal Sandstone', 'You stumble across a curious looking pile of sand thanks to your Arcane Detection Stone, and discover a Tiny Crystal Sandstone!', 1, 268, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(9, 'Discovery: Tiny Green Sandstone', 'You stumble across a curious looking pile of sand thanks to your Arcane Detection Stone, and discover a Tiny Green Sandstone!', 1, 265, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(10, 'Discovery: Tiny Red Sandstone', 'You stumble across a curious looking pile of sand thanks to your Arcane Detection Stone, and discover a Tiny Red Sandstone!', 1, 264, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(11, 'Discovery: Tiny Yellow Sandstone', 'You stumble across a curious looking pile of sand thanks to your Arcane Detection Stone, and discover a Tiny Yellow Sandstone!', 1, 267, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(12, 'The Summoning Stone', 'Beyond admiring this remarkable sight, you are unsure of what to do here.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(13, 'Frosted Whitecap Patch', 'You stumble across a patch of Frosted Whitecap mushrooms, and can''t help but take a few for yourself.', 1, 377, 3, 1000, 0, 0),
(14, 'Bandit''s Orders?', 'You come across a small and curious document along the side of the trail.  As you pick it up, you realize it''s a set of orders for bandits that patrol the area!  You realize someone at the Capital City Barracks might be very interested in seeing this.', 1, 379, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(15, 'A Vision', 'You eventually stumble back within sight of the timepiece, and are shocked to see it bathed in a thick ray of light.  With your jaw hanging open, you begin to slowly make your way to the artifact.  As you approach, the air ripples slightly, and you begin to feel warm.  To your horror, the echo of a terrible scream pierces the area, and you fall to your knees as a blinding light consumes the enclosure.  After what feels like several minutes, you open your eyes slowly, and stand.  Upon the ground in front of you is what appears to be a curious stone artifact, covered in runes.  You warily reach out, and touch the thing, half-expecting to burn your hand.  It is not hot, but in fact, quite cool to the touch.  You snatch it up, and back away warily.  What on earth was that?', 1, 385, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(16, 'Stitchweed', 'You look down, and see a small patch of Stitchweed!  Grabbing a Safeguard Rag from your pouch, you carefully scoop it up.', 1, 387, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(17, 'Sourbloom Patch', 'You catch wind of a foul odour, and look down to see a sickly looking yellow flower.  "Ah, a Sourbloom!"  You pull out one of your treated rags, and gently pluck the weed.', 1, 398, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(18, 'Álmok Crypts Chapel Doorway', 'You stand outside the entryway to the chapel, amidst a cool breeze eminating from the large structure.  A quiet movement can be heard from inside.  You steady your nerves, and prepare for the worst.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(19, 'Crypts Completed', 'The crypts are clear of danger, for the time being.  You may return tomorrow to see if the evil has risen again.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(20, 'A Terrible Piece of History', 'The crystal given to you by Warden Torgath begins to resonate, and a humming sound fills the air.  Before you know it, the earth before you begins to tremor, and a small chasm opens up.  Before you is a bright shining object!  What on earth have you found?', 1, 414, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(21, 'Entrance to the Emerald Caves', 'You stand at the entrance to the caves.  Adventuring here will bring you face-to-face with foes of considerable strength, and you steady yourself for combat.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(22, 'Caves Completed', 'The Emerald Caves are safe, once again.  However, tomorrow, the creatures will doubtless recover their strength, and return to this enchanted area.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(23, 'Burial Vaults Completed', 'The vaults are clear of danger, for the time being.  You may return tomorrow to see if the evil has risen again.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(24, 'Fractured Goldstone Relic', 'As you wander around the grounds, you discover a small relic.  It looks damaged, but you decide to take it.', 1, 452, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(25, 'Damaged Goldstone Relic', 'You stumble across a damaged piece of metal.  It is heavily worn, but you pick it up, and take it with you.', 1, 453, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(26, 'Dusty Goldstone Relic', 'A dusty old piece of material lies on the ground in front of you.  Something about it catches your eye, and you decide to pick it up and take it with you.', 1, 454, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(27, 'Cracked Goldstone Relic', 'A cracked relic sits on the ground in front of you, amidst the damage and rubble around you.  You pick it up, and take it with you.', 1, 455, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(28, 'Brittle Goldstone Relic', 'You step among the ruins, and notice a frail looking relic on the ground in front of you.  Something about it catches your eye, and you carefully pick it up.', 1, 456, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(29, 'Stables Completed', 'The stables are clear of danger, for the time being.  The summoning may yet continue; you may return tomorrow to see if the evil has risen again.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(30, 'Ancient Crystal Chain', 'A glint of light catches your eye amidst the rubble.  You stoop down to investigate..', 1, 472, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(31, 'Ancient Crystal Locket', 'A glint of light catches your eye amidst the rubble.  You stoop down to investigate..', 1, 473, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(32, 'Goldstone Depths Completed', 'You have successfully cleared out the Depths of the Goldstone Tower today.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(33, 'Damaged Entryway', 'The Collectors have been working steadily to clear the rubble, but the passage remains blocked!  You will need to wait before venturing in here.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(34, 'Grab the Crab Trap, and get out of here!', 'You sneak out into the water, and grab the trap before it floats away!  With the trap in hand, you make a hasty retreat.', 1, 752, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(35, 'Leave, and do nothing.', 'You leave, as quietly as you originally came.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(36, 'Grab the Pravokan Belt', 'You sneak in closer, grab the belt, and make a quick retreat!', 1, 753, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(37, 'Grab the Pravokan Bracers', 'You sneak in closer, grab the bracers, and make a quick retreat!', 1, 758, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(38, 'Wild Strawberry', 'You carefully pluck the delicate berry, and place it in your inventory.', 1, 762, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(39, 'Violet Starleaf', 'You sneak up to the starleaf, cautiously remove the flower, and make your retreat.', 1, 763, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(40, 'Yellow Trillium', 'You sneak up to the flower, and cautiously pluck it from the ground.', 1, 764, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(41, 'Grab the Pravokan Timber', 'You wait until the Pravokan wanders off, and scoop up the timber!', 1, 778, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(43, 'Take the Left Treasury Path', 'You take a deep breath, and begin your journey down the left path.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 55, 28),
(44, 'Take the Center Treasury Path', 'You take a deep breath, and begin your journey down the center path.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 55, 29),
(45, 'Take the Right Treasury Path', 'You take a deep breath, and begin your journey down the right path.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 55, 30),
(46, 'Lost Treasury Cleared', 'You have scoured the Lost Treasury of demonic forces for today, but you don''t doubt that if you return tomorrow, more foes will have come to claim the ancient treasures found here.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(47, 'Tul''um Rubble Pile', 'You spot a large pile of shattered goods, but only come up with crumbling dust.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0),
(48, 'Tul''um Dirt Pile', 'You spot a large pile of dirt, but only come up with crumbling dust.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0),
(49, 'Tul''um Ceramic Pile', 'You spot what appears to be a large pile of shattered ceramic goods, and when you investigate, manage to find a salvageable piece.', 1, 820, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(50, 'Tul''um Ceramic Piece', 'As you hunt around the area, you spot what appears to be a pristine ceramic piece.  You cautiously inch over, and delicately pick it up.', 1, 821, 1, 1000, 0, 0),
(51, 'The Great Labyrinth', 'You enter the halls cautiously, but are stunned to discover that the great corridors are empty.  A collection of bolts and metal scraps lie strewn across the floors, but you find no sign of movement here.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(52, 'Use your Great Labyrinth Key', 'You walk up to the curious doorway, and insert the key into a small hole in the wall that matches the pattern.  Something behind the walls begins to hum, and a vicious grating sound erupts from the doorway!  Your key is crushed as the stone shifts around, and a gust of stale air rushes out of the new entrance.  For today at least, the way to the labyrinth is open.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 60, 6),
(53, 'Do nothing', 'You decide to wait for now.  From what you can tell, each key gets only a single use, as the locking mechanism on the massive structure is designed to destroy any trace of an adventurer''s entrance.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(55, 'Shift the lever''s position UP', 'You grasp the lever in your hands, and push against it with a great deal of force.  The lever begins to budge, and shifts to the upper position.  You hear a series of grinding noises from deep within the labyrinth.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 60, 7),
(54, 'Enter the Great Labyrinth', 'With the doorway opened, you decide to venture inside to investigate.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(56, 'Shift the lever''s position DOWN', 'You grasp the lever in your hands, and pull on it with the full weight of your body.  The lever begins to budge, and shifts to the lower position.  You hear a series of grinding noises from deep within the labyrinth.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 60, 8),
(57, 'Shift the lever''s position UP', 'You grasp the lever in your hands, and push against it with a great deal of force. The lever begins to budge, and shifts to the upper position. You hear a series of grinding noises from deep within the labyrinth.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 60, 9),
(58, 'Shift the lever''s position DOWN', 'You grasp the lever in your hands, and pull on it with the full weight of your body. The lever begins to budge, and shifts to the lower position. You hear a series of grinding noises from deep within the labyrinth.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 60, 10),
(59, 'Shift the lever''s position UP', 'You grasp the lever in your hands, and push against it with a great deal of force. The lever begins to budge, and shifts to the upper position. You hear a series of grinding noises from deep within the labyrinth.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 60, 11),
(60, 'Shift the lever''s position DOWN', 'You grasp the lever in your hands, and pull on it with the full weight of your body. The lever begins to budge, and shifts to the lower position. You hear a series of grinding noises from deep within the labyrinth.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 60, 12),
(61, 'Shift the lever''s position UP', 'You grasp the lever in your hands, and push against it with a great deal of force. The lever begins to budge, and shifts to the upper position. You hear a series of grinding noises from deep within the labyrinth.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 60, 13),
(62, 'Shift the lever''s position DOWN', 'You grasp the lever in your hands, and pull on it with the full weight of your body. The lever begins to budge, and shifts to the lower position. You hear a series of grinding noises from deep within the labyrinth.', 0, 0, 0, 1000, 60, 14);
INSERT INTO `zones` (`id`, `parent_id`, `parent_name`, `name`, `description`, `zone_type`, `min_level`, `ui_order`, `artifact_required`, `entry_check`, `dev`) VALUES
(1, 0, '', 'Capital City', 'You stand at the center of town.  The city bustles with activity, as people move between districts.  Up ahead lies the Market District, where you can purchase things like armour and weapons, trade goods, and other artifacts you may need in your travels.  The Academy towers lie off to the west, the source of knowledge and skills in the land.  A collection of other shops and stores lie around you.', 1, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(2, 1, 'Capital City', 'Thog''s Weapons', 'The weaponmaster, a strong warrior named Thog, maintains a tiny store filled with weapons of varying quality.', 2, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(3, 1, 'Capital City', 'Turagon''s Trinkets', 'A clumsy assortment of gadgets litters the shop.  You step around the scattered pieces on the ground, and make your way to the merchant.', 2, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(4, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Peaceful Meadows', 'A light breeze moves through these open fields just outside of town.  Although they''ve been named the Peaceful Meadows, several bands of kobolds have made their home here.  Even the docile animals have begun to revolt against their presence.  You keep a watchful eye.', 4, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(5, 1, 'Capital City', 'Hard Zone', 'This is a really hard zone.  If you''re here, then..  wow..  Nice work.', 4, 9999, 10, 0, 0, 1),
(6, 1, 'Capital City', 'Gemmaville', 'Lovely Gemma owns this part of town.  She is lovely, and kind, and all her peasants love her.', 3, 30, 20, 23, 0, 1),
(7, 1, 'Capital City', 'Capital City Infirmary', 'It takes some time to wade through the groups of wounded adventurers, but you eventually find your way to a doctor.', 100, 1, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(8, 4, 'The Peaceful Meadows', 'Disorganized Kobold Camp', 'The kobolds are not known for their decorative sense, and the camp appears to have been hastily constructed.', 3, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(9, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Grand Academy', 'As you enter the main hallway of the academy, you almost feel as though your breath has been taken away.  The architecture is stunning, and masterpieces of artwork line every hallway.  Signs on the corridors indicate which direction will lead you to which aspect of training you wish to explore.', 102, 1, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(10, 4, 'The Peaceful Meadows', 'Abandoned Farmhouse', 'A family of sturdy farmers used to live here, tending the fields, and managing their animals.  From what you can gather, this is no longer the case; undead seem to have taken over the area.  Whether or not it is the family maintaining their claim on the land or not, you aren''t sure.  However, you know the place is not safe!', 3, 2, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(11, 1, 'Capital City', 'House of Defense', 'This large stone building is littered with various pieces of well-made armour.  The merchant looks at you with a tough glare, gauging whether or not you have the funds to make a purchase today.', 2, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(12, 4, 'The Peaceful Meadows', 'Fortified Iron Hand Rebel Camp', 'This area acts as a central location for a band of hooligans and thieves who strive to make things difficult for traders moving in and out of town.  They seem well equipped, wearing armour and weapons of varying quality.', 3, 3, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(13, 1, 'Capital City', 'Hall of Records', 'This building feels like a library.  It is filled to the brim with census records and populace details about residents throughout the land.  As you stand, gaping at the collection of tomes and records, a worker notices you and smiles.  "And to think, we still somehow manage to update our records every hour, on the hour!  Excuse me, speaking of which, it''s time to get back to work!"', 101, 1, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(14, 4, 'The Peaceful Meadows', 'Omor''s Forest (Western Edge)', 'Ahead, the forest appears almost threatening.  You begin to enter the underbrush, and notice a distinctly less friendly atmosphere from the meadows to your west.  You remain on your guard while walking in to the dense growth.', 4, 4, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(15, 14, 'Omor''s Forest (Western Edge)', 'Cavernous Bear Cave', 'This large and surprisingly natural cavern appears to have been taken over by a large pack of bears.  Seeking safety from the dangers of the forest here may have been a wise idea for them, but not for you!', 3, 5, 21, 0, 0, 0),
(16, 14, 'Omor''s Forest (Western Edge)', 'Abandoned Copper Fields', 'This fields lie outside of an old mine that collapsed many years ago, leaving countless workers to die.  Although it is true that they found death here, they did not find peace, and now roam as undead.', 3, 5, 21, 0, 0, 0),
(17, 14, 'Omor''s Forest (Western Edge)', 'Deteriorated Forest Trail', 'A damaged pathway through the dark depths of Omor''s Forest.  The trail must have been in heavy use years ago, but has since fallen into disrepair.  The wilderness has taken over what was once a well-groomed dirt trail, and the animals don''t take kindly to humans reclaiming old territories!', 3, 4, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(18, 14, 'Omor''s Forest (Western Edge)', 'Omor''s Forest (Heart)', 'The air feels heavy with the residue of arcane energy.  From your understanding, the Sands of Omor are nearby, and they appear to hold an influence on the neighbouring lands even after all these ages.', 4, 6, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(19, 4, 'The Peaceful Meadows', 'Green Creek', 'The run-off from the rapids of the Green River have formed these beautiful lands over the course of time.  The distance to Capital City isn''t that great, but even some minor wildlife have turned hostile.  You remain on guard, but can not prevent yourself from admiring the beauty of the lush greenery around you.', 4, 9999, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(20, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Bustling Farmlands', 'The wild and open farmlands of the diligent and hardworking citizens of the capital lay in front of you.  Life here is not easy, but those among the workers here count themselves fortunate to make an honest day''s pay.  Around you, farmers work the soil, and develop the lands so that food can reach the mouths of the city dwellers.', 4, 2, 11, 0, 0, 0),
(21, 20, 'The Bustling Farmlands', 'The Wild Meadows', 'Unlike the sister lands to the north, the Wild Meadows have earned their name due to the abundance of predators who roam the lands.  The nearby farmers leave wide open spaces filled with food, and have left themselves open to some degree of pillaging.  You remain on your guard.', 4, 3, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(22, 4, 'The Peaceful Meadows', 'Green River', 'Perhaps due to the amazing plantlife in the area, or maybe some chemical reaction in the water, the waters of the river have been given a name that suits them well.  The deep emerald lakes flow slowly but surely, and have given rise to a number of various communities of life along its edge.', 4, 3, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(23, 22, 'Green River', 'Green Pond', 'The mighty waters of the Green River pool here inland into this majestic pond.  The emerald waters have given life to a wonderous and diverse amount of wildlife, ranging from unique and dangerous creatures to overgrown plants seeming to hold minds of their own.  Perhaps the Sands of Omor due south are not too far away to hold some influence over the waters.', 4, 5, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(24, 23, 'Green Pond', 'Omor''s Forest (Northern Edge)', 'The dangers of Omor''s Forest are no less present on the northern side, and the dense underbrush is a reminder of the wilds that lie within.', 4, 5, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(25, 20, 'The Bustling Farmlands', 'Merchant''s Line', 'The dusty old trail leads out of Capital City and on to lands in need of the wares of traveling salespeople.  The roads are often plagued by looters and pillagers, and you remind yourself to maintain your wits while moving along the roads.', 4, 2, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(26, 25, 'Merchant''s Line', 'The Vile Meadows', 'The Vile Meadows have become a desolate land, trapped between cities, and home only to an expanding field of swamps.', 4, 7, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(64, 26, 'The Vile Meadows', 'The Vile Swamplands (Entrance)', 'You peer in to the entrance to the swamps, and feel almost overcome with illness.  The area teems with rotting plants, and stinks of death.', 3, 7, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(27, 14, 'Omor''s Forest (Western Edge)', 'Omor''s Defense', 'Viewed by some as the last bastion of safety against the true nature of the Sands of Omor, the Defense acts as a home for those who seek to reclaim the lands and act as a barrier between the horrors of the desert and the civilization west of here.', 4, 8, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(28, 27, 'Omor''s Defense', 'The Sands of Omor (Northern Edge)', 'The legends of the lands could not have prepared you for this glimpse into the barren deserts of the nearest of the Sands to civilization.  The climate is harsh, and the winds ahead appear unceasing.  Life here has taken a turn for the worst, and those beings who have survived seem hardened due to the nature of the Sands.', 4, 9, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(29, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Market District', 'People rush among each other through the shopping district of Capital City.  There are a number of shops here, ranging from armour and weaponry, to more exotic goods.  You glance around at the storefronts available to you.', 1, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(30, 22, 'Green River', 'The Misted Shores', 'An eerie silence falls over the shoreline here.  The emerald water seeps along slowly, but no wind seems to disturb the light haze that falls over this land.', 3, 3, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(31, 22, 'Green River', 'The Overgrown Underbrush', 'Whether due to something in the water, or some other artifact of the area, the life in this spot has begun to grow out of proportion.  You feel quite small in these wilds!', 3, 9999, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(32, 29, 'The Market District', 'Bidwell''s Eatery', 'As you enter, you find yourself greeted by Barnabus Bidwell, eccentric chef of the Eatery.  Day in and day out, he works feverishly to bring the best in culinary sensations to the people of Capital City.  The smell of freshly baked breads, savoury sauces, and fresh herbs is overwhelming.', 2, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(33, 29, 'The Market District', 'Arcanery and Enchanted Goods', 'You can almost feel the air buzzing with arcane magic, and the sheer number of artifacts in this small shop fills you with wonder.  Some glow, some seem to hum with their own forces, and all seem to beckon you in some way.', 2, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(34, 23, 'Green Pond', 'Enchanted Nook', 'Some form of residual magic seems to have enchanted the area, imbuing the creatures with great power.', 3, 7, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(35, 23, 'Green Pond', 'Base of the Green Waterfall', 'Some part of the Green River has found its way into the heart of Omor''s Forest, and combined with the enchanted energies of the region, has produced some alarming forms of life.', 3, 8, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(36, 29, 'The Market District', 'Trade Goods and Services', 'This shop is a professional''s paradise, with a collection of goods available to help you with crafts or construction.', 2, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(37, 1, 'Capital City', 'Tranquility Park', 'In the middle of a large bustling city can often be found a truly serene place of contemplation.  Tranquility Park is a restful place, filled with lush greenery and gentle ponds.  People have seated themselves throughout the area, resting or reading, and generally enjoying themselves peacefully.', 1, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(38, 37, 'Tranquility Park', 'The Tranquil Pond', 'Several schools of small fish dart across the surface of the water.', 5, 1, 30, 0, 0, 0),
(39, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Capital Casino', 'Amidst a sea of sparklers, vendors, and buskers, you find a brightly coloured building which seems filled to capacity.  Some smile, and wave around large sacks of gold, while others seem either depressed or angry, scowling at the winners.  Your eyes light up at the possibility of untold riches.  A number of large tables with seemingly larger men behind them open up to you.  The price seems steep, but you''ve seen others win dramatic fortunes at these tables, and wonder if today is your time to succeed.  You debate taking a seat, and count the change on your person once more.', 103, 4, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(40, 22, 'The Green River', 'The Descending Coves', 'This part of the river is filled with waters that are surprisingly stirred up.  You stand upon some elevated hills, before descending down into a cove along the somewhat isolated base of the Green River itself.', 4, 9, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(41, 22, 'Green River', 'The Green River Shorelines', 'Standing above the hills felt much safer than in this area, populated with dangerous waterlife that has ventured out into drier lands.', 3, 5, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(42, 40, 'The Descending Coves', 'The Rushing Rapids', 'Moving out into the waters on some slim stones has exposed some of the more dangerous creatures in the Green River.', 3, 9, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(43, 22, 'Green River', 'The Undying Timepiece', 'In the center of a curious opening in the dense trees lies a single stone sundial.  Despite the relative lack of sunlight in the area, somehow the timepiece still registers the time of day with a light shadow.', 4, 4, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(44, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Auction House', 'In many ways, this is the center of economic activity in the town.  People rush back and forth between auctioneers, querying costs and quantites in search of a great deal or a rare item from across the land.', 104, 3, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(45, 1, 'Capital City', 'Badges and Awards', 'Plaques and ribbons adorn the walls of this small building.  Among the awards covering the walls, you see references to heroes and champions from across the world.  Before you know it, you''ve begun dreaming of the day your name will be seen here.', 105, 1, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(46, 43, 'The Undying Timepiece', 'The Undying Timepiece (Morning)', 'The morning side of the timepiece sets off into a relatively calm and light forested area.', 3, 4, 21, 0, 0, 0),
(47, 43, 'The Undying Timepiece', 'The Undying Timepiece (Mid-Day)', 'The mid-day side of the timepiece appears fairly well-lit, and reasonably well covered by the forestry.', 3, 6, 22, 0, 0, 0),
(48, 43, 'The Undying Timepiece', 'The Undying Timepiece (Evening)', 'The evening side of the timepiece is quite well covered in a dense overgrowth of trees.', 3, 8, 23, 0, 0, 0),
(49, 43, 'The Undying Timepiece', 'The Undying Timepiece (Night)', 'The forest falls in to heavy darkness here, apparently even in a well-lit day.  You understand that venturing in here requires a very strong heart.', 3, 10, 24, 0, 0, 0),
(50, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Capital Barracks', 'The structure itself looks quite plain from the outside, but from the number of well-outfitted guards patrolling the area, you can tell its importance.  Several large figures stand around, looking to put people to work.', 1, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(51, 27, 'Omor''s Defense', 'The Iron Hand Outpost', 'It appears that the Iron Hand have also decided that the Sands of Omor warrant an outpost for observation.  The camp is well guarded, and well patrolled.', 3, 8, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(52, 27, 'Omor''s Defense', 'The Sand Mines', 'It isn''t immediately clear to you what the goal of these mines is, but you are able to discern a tremendous amount of Iron Hand activity in the area.', 3, 9, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(53, 28, 'The Sands of Omor (Northern Edge)', 'The Sand Mines (Earth Tear)', 'Some form of earthquake or geyser has opened up a crack in to the mines from the Sands.  It looks ominous, but you can definitely find your way inside from here.', 3, 10, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(54, 20, 'The Bustling Farmlands', 'The Boar Fields', 'A wide expanse of open fields, with a seemingly unending set of boar families roaming the area.  They are regarded as responsible for driving out a number of the farmers from the area, and are held in very low regard.', 3, 2, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(55, 21, 'The Wild Meadows', 'Savage Plains', 'While this area is quite wide and open, it appears to have been taken over by the wildlife of the area, who appear completely unconcerned with your appearance.', 3, 3, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(56, 1, 'Capital City', 'Initiate''s Corridors', 'Among the wide corridors of the large building, you see many young adventurers preparing to make their way into the world.  You should find the equipment needed to succeed nearby.', 1, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(57, 56, 'Initiate''s Corridors', 'The Weapon House', 'A full suite of training and simple combat weapons sits before you.  You take time to inspect each one, and carefully consider which you might need for the upcoming dangers.', 2, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(58, 56, 'Initiate''s Corridors', 'The Armour House', 'You see many different sets of armour, and consider how much protection you are currently wearing.  Perhaps it might be time to buy something new!', 2, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(59, 22, 'Green River', 'Shallow Emerald Ponds', 'A collection of beautiful pools of water.  You catch rare glimpses of fish jumping to the surface, and understand that it will take some skill to fish in this area.', 5, 5, 30, 0, 0, 0),
(60, 39, 'The Capital Casino', 'Casino Merchandise', 'This area is decidedly less fun than the casino itself, heavily guarded, and crammed with protective steel bars.  You notice a stone-faced merchant, who appears ready to exchange your winnings for unique goods from the casino.', 7, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(61, 14, 'Omor`s Forest (Western Edge)', 'Abandoned Mine Entrance', 'It looks as though this used to be an entrance in to the copper mines below the forest, but caved in at some point.  A tight remnant of the old entrance now remains.', 6, 6, 40, 0, 0, 0),
(62, 27, 'Omor''s Defense', 'Sandstorm Outpost', 'A small but well-defended outpost, held by members of the Sandstorm clan.', 3, 8, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(63, 43, 'The Undying Timepiece', 'The Undying Pools', 'A stagnant set of pools that somehow continue to support life.', 5, 8, 30, 0, 0, 0),
(65, 26, 'The Vile Meadows', 'The Vile Swamplands (Depths)', 'The area stinks of death, but holds an eerie silence.', 3, 8, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(66, 29, 'The Market District', 'Capital City Rewards Hall', 'A large collection of valuables line the walls of this hall.  Treasures meant for the dearest patrons of the city are available to those who have earned them.', 7, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(67, 26, 'The Vile Meadows', 'The Vile Undermines', 'Sickly remnants of an old mine.  You surprise yourself by finding a path that could be traversed down into the stinking depths.', 6, 9, 40, 0, 0, 0),
(68, 27, 'Omor''s Defense', 'The Sandguard Storehouse', 'A collection of well-built armour and weaponry is kept under heavy guard here.  Gaining honour in their ranks will entitle you to a piece of the rewards.', 7, 8, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(69, 50, 'The Capital Barracks', 'The Undeath Wards', 'The man behind the counter is a pale and gaunt individual, but the artifacts littered around the area amaze you.', 7, 5, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(70, 29, 'The Market District', 'Veteran''s Market', 'This area is closed off to the younger population, in order to showcase better artifacts used when facing even greater challenges.  It''s almost intimidating, seeing so many of the town heroes in one place.', 1, 8, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(71, 70, 'Veteran''s Market', 'Heavy Armour Storefront', 'A collection of durable armours crafted in mail and plate.', 2, 9, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(72, 70, 'Veteran''s Market', 'Veteran''s Armoury', 'Armour sets line the walls of this large store.  You see the Heavy Armour Storefront across the street, and note that it''s there where the mail and plate is held.', 2, 9, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(73, 26, 'The Vile Meadows', 'The Vile Swamplands (Heart)', 'You step in to the heart of the swamplands, and are repulsed by the stench of decay that surrounds you.', 3, 9, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(74, 70, 'Veteran''s Market', 'Unique Weaponry', 'This store is full of weapons that require a specific skill to use, like swords and wands.', 2, 8, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(75, 1, 'Capital City', 'City Hall', 'The large marble building houses most of the governmental facilities of the town.', 1, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(76, 70, 'Veteran''s Market', 'Edouard''s Weaponsmithing', 'The shop is home to a well-respected customization expert in Capital City.  Edouard specializes in reworking existing weapons into something new and more powerful.', 7, 9, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(77, 28, 'The Sands of Omor (Northern Edge)', 'Deserted Guard''s Barracks', 'This was once one of the outposts guarding Omor''s Citadel, a spire jutting forth from the glassed sands in the distance.  However, it has since fallen, and has been overrun with Webweaver Spiders.', 3, 10, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(78, 29, 'The Market District', 'Fish Market', 'It looks like the ponds have been kind to local fishers, who have a few extra catches available!', 2, 9999, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(79, 28, 'The Sands of Omor (Northern Edge)', 'Citadel of Omor', 'A daunting stone citadel that stretches up towards the sky.', 4, 11, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(80, 79, 'Citadel of Omor', 'Omor''s Courtyard', 'This appears to have once been a beautiful piece of open space, but has now been darkened and infested with a collection of large beetle-like creatures.  You catch flickers of movement from the shadows that fill the space.', 3, 11, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(81, 79, 'Citadel of Omor', 'The Great Labyrinth', 'A sprawling web of walls and mechanical parts.  You can only imagine the original intent of this massive space, but it appears to have fallen in to complete disarray.', 3, 11, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(82, 28, 'The Sands of Omor (Northern Edge)', 'The Fiery Moats', 'A simmering expanse of molten rock.  The area is infested with demons.', 3, 10, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(83, 79, 'Citadel of Omor', 'Upper Citadel of Omor', 'This daunting series of chambers and corridors threatens to send your head spinning.  Although the great citadel appeared to be a massive structure from the outside, you wonder how it could possibly hold such a vast expanse.  You steel your nerves, and glance around at the places to go from here.', 4, 12, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(84, 83, 'Upper Citadel of Omor', 'Omor''s Summoning Chamber', 'Seated at the center of this great room is a large runed tablet.  The shapes are beautiful, complex, and well-preserved.  Runes cover the floor, and to your shock, also adorn the walls and ceiling.', 3, 12, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(85, 50, 'The Capital Barracks', 'Training Fields', 'These small grasslands offer a warrior the chance to test their mettle against seasoned veterans of Capital City.', 3, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(86, 14, 'Omor''s Forest (Western Edge)', 'Abandoned Copper Depths', 'After the collapse of the mine, and the death of the workers, the area fell into a deep undeath.  What occurs within the deep and nearly forgotten corridors is unwelcoming to the living.', 3, 6, 22, 0, 0, 0),
(87, 23, 'Green Pond', 'Álmok Crypts', 'The Álmok Crypts were opened, and filled to capacity shortly after the decimation that led to the creation of the Sands.  Countless lives were lost, and many of the bodies were brought here to rest.  What is troubling is that the souls of those laid to rest have not all found peace.', 4, 6, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(88, 87, 'Álmok Crypts', 'Álmok Crypts Chapel', 'A heavy layer of dust coats the room, from the rotting pews up to the yellowing stained glass windows, now mostly broken.', 8, 6, 50, 0, 0, 0),
(89, 87, 'Álmok Crypts', 'Álmok Crypts Burial Vaults', 'The air inside the tomb is filled with a thick dust, and you are assaulted by the acrid smell of decay.', 8, 9, 50, 0, 0, 0),
(90, 87, 'Álmok Crypts', 'Zsuzsa''s Cart', '"I''m interested in the tokens you''ll find in the crypts.  Bring them to me, and we might be able to make a deal on some unique trades."', 7, 6, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(91, 70, 'Veteran''s Market', 'The Stables', 'Horses and other riding creatures are kept here.', 7, 8, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(92, 22, 'Green River', 'Emerald Caves', 'A wonderous looking area, with bright green stones adorning the cave walls.  That said, you remain cautious, wary of the dangerous foes that lurk within.', 8, 3, 50, 0, 0, 0),
(93, 22, 'Green River', 'Katalin''s Goods', 'Katalin offers a humble selection of jewelry crafted by her own hand.', 7, 3, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(94, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Great Treasury', 'In order to show respect to those who have donated to the longevity of the land, the champions of the city have set up a treasury where adventurers can receive gifts of great quality.  You are awed by the regal hall.', 7, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(95, 25, 'Merchant''s Line', 'Goldstone Ruins', 'Before the lands were reshaped by history, a vast network of traders and merchants made this land their home.  Now, the area is held by a sparse group of bandits, and a group from the Collectors, who seek to regain riches now believed lost.', 4, 11, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(96, 95, 'Goldstone Ruins', 'Barracks of the Collectors', 'It appears as though the organization has set up a well-fortified barracks in order to build a formidible offense against the bandits.', 1, 11, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(97, 96, 'Barracks of the Collectors', 'The Reclaimed Vault', 'A very well guarded stash of goods, used by the Collectors in their struggle to reclaim the ruins.', 7, 11, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(98, 95, 'Goldstone Ruins', 'Bandit''s Haunt', 'The primary set of structures originally designed to house the merchants have been claimed by a tough gang of bandits.', 3, 11, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(99, 95, 'Goldstone Ruins', 'The Decimated Vaults', 'At the heart of the ruins lie a set of vaults, once used to hold the most valuable treasures under heavy lock and key.', 3, 12, 20, 507, 0, 0),
(100, 95, 'Goldstone Ruins', 'Ruins of the Goldstone Tower', 'The spiral still stands tall, but pieces of the lookout post have begun to crumble, and the structure almost appears to lean against the clouded sky.', 3, 13, 20, 508, 0, 0),
(101, 95, 'Goldstone Ruins', 'Depths of the Goldstone Tower', 'A deep basement lies below the tower.  What is held there now lies beyond even the reach of the bandits.', 8, 13, 50, 509, 0, 0),
(102, 87, 'Álmok Crypts', 'Álmok Crypts Stables', 'After the raiding against the crypts began, sentient forces began to well up some resistance, and the evil contained in the depths called out for aid.  The bones of an old set of elite riders are regaining their lost power.', 8, 12, 50, 0, 0, 0),
(104, 9, 'The Grand Academy', 'Pathfinder''s Hall', 'You manage to track your way to a more subdued area of the academy.  Curiously, the air here seems to hum with a strange energy.  Scattered groups of adventurers and scholars stand around, some looking dazed, and others looking deep in thought.', 1, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(103, 40, 'The Descending Coves', 'Red Clay Caves', 'Something in the earth has set a rich red hue into the walls and floors.  The air is acrid and dry, and few sounds pass through the crimson caves.', 4, 10, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(105, 104, 'Pathfinder`s Hall', 'Pathfinder''s Onyx Storefront', 'You gasp as you enter the small building.  The treasures here are truly wonderous.', 7, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(106, 1, 'Capital City', 'Bank of Nobility', 'Finely dressed businessfolk stroll around the floors of this stunning marble building.  You notice a massive vault behind a force of the finest city guards.  If you''re looking to lock up your goods, this is the place to do it!', 107, 1, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(107, 104, 'Pathfinder''s Hall', 'The Temporal Laboratory', 'The room contains a small handful of people.  Their differences in age comes as a surprise to you; even the young scholars here wield what appear to be fantastic and tremendously powerful artifacts!  It might be worth your while to learn more about what is being studied here..', 106, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(108, 39, 'The Capital Casino', 'The Games Room', 'A bunch of people seem to be setting up tables here..', 108, 4, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(109, 20, 'The Bustling Farmlands', 'Sandstorm Fortification', 'In order to make inroads against Capital City, it appears the Sandstorm forces are constructing a fortification outside of town!', 109, 2, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(110, 1, 'Capital City', 'Nico''s Excavation Site', 'A shambling collection of tools stands at the precipice to the chasm in the sands.  It looks as though a great excavation site was being planned here, but was hastily abandoned.  A small handful of workers remain, toiling about, in an effort to salvage whatever goods can be saved.', 4, 11, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(111, 110, 'Nico''s Excavation Site', 'Scarshield Staircases', 'In order to gain entrance to the lower corridors of the Scarshield, the guardians here must be eliminated.', 110, 11, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(112, 111, 'Scarshield Staircases', 'Lost Storage Halls', 'This appears to have been the first site of entry into the planned excavation.  It is littered with damaged and destroyed goods, spent blasting equipment, and scorched or rusted tools.  From the deep corridors comes the sound of a thousand cackling voices..', 3, 11, 20, 0, 1, 0),
(113, 1, 'Capital City', 'The Westerly Trails', 'A series of well-worn trails heading west, towards the coastlines and hills near the water.', 4, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(114, 113, 'The Westerly Trails', 'Starfall Bay Coastlines', 'The legends surrounding the great bay tell of a mighty star that fell from the sky and created this body of water.  The coastline appears to have softened over time, although patches of rough rock still remain.', 4, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(115, 113, 'The Westerly Trails', 'Starfall Bay Trading Company', 'In an attempt to help foster trade between the residents of Capital City and nearby villages, a group of enterprising individuals have set up a shipping and trading company with exotic goods from around the world.  You can return at any time to bid on rare goods that you won''t have much luck finding through normal means!', 4, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(116, 115, 'Starfall Bay Trading Company', 'Starfall Auction Courts', 'The main trading hall of the company.  You can make bids on exotic goods here, when they''re available.', 111, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(117, 6, 'Gemmaville', 'Dev Fishing', 'Development Fishing Zone', 5, 30, 10, 0, 0, 1),
(118, 114, 'Starfall Bay Coastlines', 'Drifting Weeds', 'A bustling patch of seaweed drifts through the water, and appears to be teeming with life.', 5, 10, 30, 0, 0, 0),
(119, 114, 'Starfall Bay Coastlines', 'Starfall Crab Coasts', 'A collection of well-equipped pirates seem to have laid claim to these coasts, in order to collect a formidible bounty in crab meat!', 3, 10, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(120, 114, 'Starfall Bay Coastlines', 'Algas Island', 'In an attempt to train the pirate scourge, they have set up a number of bases on this island, and combat with the ferocious life that already lives here.  The shores are well fortified, but further entrance into the land appears difficult!', 3, 11, 20, 0, 2, 0),
(121, 114, 'Starfall Bay Coastlines', 'Eldras Island', 'This looks like the main base of the Pravokan Pirates!  It is extremely well fortified from the water, and if you intend on getting in here, you''re going to need to find some way of disguising yourself.', 3, 11, 20, 0, 3, 0),
(122, 115, 'Starfall Bay Trading Company', 'Starfall Exchange', 'A small storefront where a changing supply of goods can be bartered.', 7, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(123, 39, 'The Capital Casino', 'Capital City Lottery Company', 'Capital City holds a grand lottery three times a week, and welcomes any interested players for a chance to win big!', 112, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(124, 111, 'Scarshield Staircases', 'Lost Treasury', 'In order to store the wealth of goods used in the excavation, a grand treasury was established.  It has fallen into disuse, but some hope of reclaiming the treasure remains.', 8, 11, 50, 0, 1, 0),
(125, 113, 'The Westerly Trails', 'The Starfall Plains', 'A wide span of lush grassland that appears to have been trampled by some recent warfare.', 4, 11, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(126, 125, 'The Starfall Plains', 'Pravokan Revelry', 'Apparently this is where the Pravokan pirates like to visit when they get a little free time.  Broken bottles and waste products litter the trampled ground.', 113, 11, 100, 0, 0, 0),
(127, 50, 'The Capital Barracks', 'Allied Contracting', 'With an excess of military force currently existing in the city, a group of combatants have made themselves available for hire.', 7, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(128, 113, 'The Westerly Trails', 'Outskirts of Tul''um', 'A dense forest area, littered with the crushed bones and shattered artifacts of a lost empire.', 1, 30, 10, 0, 0, 1),
(129, 128, 'Outskirts of Tul''um', 'Tul''um Outer Gates', 'A wide span of land, littered with broken pieces of history.', 3, 30, 20, 0, 0, 1),
(130, 28, 'The Sands of Omor (Northern Edge)', 'Entrance to the Great Labyrinth', 'Two massive pillars guide you toward the labyrinth itself, a sprawling web of walls and mechanical parts.', 4, 11, 10, 0, 0, 0),
(131, 130, 'Entrance to the Great Labyrinth', 'The Great Labyrinth', 'An imposing structure, filled with a twisting set of corridors designed to confuse and trap the most experienced of adventurers.', 8, 11, 50, 0, 0, 0),
(132, 28, 'The Sands of Omor (Northern Edge)', 'Jorge''s Cart', 'Jorge watches you, as you consider whether to purchase a key to the Great Labyrinth.', 7, 11, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(133, 1, 'Capital City', 'Runes and Relics', 'This heavy stone building stands tall and intimidating in the streets, encrusted with detailed scripts of all shapes and sizes.  It houses a number of runes that can be used to grant you special magical abilities.', 7, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(134, 70, 'Veteran''s Market', 'Runes and Other Curiosities', 'A small storefront sits amidst the larger weapon and armour stores.  Upon its stone walls are furiously detailed markings, slightly luminescent in the shadows.', 7, 8, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(135, 7, 'Capital City Infirmary', 'Doc''s Supplies', 'A small office in the infirmary holds a collection of medical supplies being made available to adventurers.', 7, 1, 20, 0, 0, 0),
(136, 25, 'Merchant''s Line', 'Crumbling Path to Dunnich', 'A well-trodden and overgrown path catches your eye.  Surely the trail has not been used regularly for decades.  A careful step and a watchful eye is necessary to travel this road.', 4, 12, 10, 0, 0, 1),
(137, 136, 'Crumbling Path to Dunnich', 'Dunnich Front Fortification', 'The crumbling gates of Dunnich stand before you.  In the worn and dying fields, endless fields of wisps stream back and forth, hunting for remnants of life.', 3, 12, 20, 0, 0, 1),
(138, 136, 'Crumbling Path to Dunnich', 'Dunnich Guard Tower', 'The rocky ruins of the guard tower are well protected by the wisps, although they stream less hungrily than the ones from the fortification.', 3, 12, 20, 0, 4, 1),
(139, 136, 'Crumbling Path to Dunnich', 'Dunnich Town Square', 'The haunted ruins of the town of Dunnich now stand silent.  As you glance back to the entrance, you note the wisps streaming in their endless hunt for life.  In front of you are the dilapitated structures that once formed a thriving town.', 4, 12, 10, 0, 4, 1),
(140, 113, 'The Westerly Trails', 'Starfall Properties', 'The lucrative Starfall Bay Trading Company are establishing a secure set of properties on the coast, for travelers who are hunting for a place of their own.  If you own a land deed, you can set up your own tract of land here on Starfall Bay.', 114, 1, 10, 0, 0, 0);
